2025-12-09|Filter and Sort Valid Coupons by Business Line

Question
You are given three arrays of length n that describe the properties of n coupons: code, businessLine, and isActive.
A coupon is valid if:
-	code is non-empty and alphanumeric with underscores only,
-	businessLine is one of "electronics", "grocery", "pharmacy", "restaurant",
-	isActive is true.
Return the valid coupon codes sorted by businessLine order and then lexicographically.

Approach
1.	Define a fixed priority order for businessLine:
	-	electronics → 0
	-	grocery → 1
	-	pharmacy → 2
	-	restaurant → 3
2.	Iterate over all coupons and validate each one:
	-	Check isActive is true.
	-	Check code is non-empty and every character is alphanumeric or '_'.
	-	Check businessLine exists in the allowed category list.
3.	For every valid coupon, store:
	-	The priority index of its businessLine.
	-	The coupon code.
4.	Sort all valid coupons:
	-	Primary key: businessLine priority.
	-	Secondary key: coupon code (ascending).
5.	Extract and return only the coupon codes.
6.	Time complexity: O(n log n).
   Space complexity: O(n).

Solution
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> validCoupons(vector<string>& code,
                                vector<string>& businessLine,
                                vector<bool>& isActive) {

        unordered_map<string, int> priority = {
            {"electronics", 0},
            {"grocery", 1},
            {"pharmacy", 2},
            {"restaurant", 3}
        };

        vector<pair<int, string>> valid;

        int n = code.size();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (!isActive[i]) continue;

            // check business line
            if (priority.find(businessLine[i]) == priority.end())
                continue;

            // check code validity
            if (code[i].empty()) continue;
            bool ok = true;
            for (char c : code[i]) {
                if (!isalnum(c) && c != '_') {
                    ok = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (!ok) continue;

            valid.push_back({priority[businessLine[i]], code[i]});
        }

        sort(valid.begin(), valid.end(),
             [](const pair<int,string>& a, const pair<int,string>& b) {
                 if (a.first != b.first)
                     return a.first < b.first;
                 return a.second < b.second;
             });

        vector<string> result;
        for (auto &p : valid)
            result.push_back(p.second);

        return result;
    }
};
